<item>
            <title>[HBASE-1576] TIF needs to be able to set scanner caching size for smaller row tables &amp; performance</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1576</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;TIF goes with the default scanner caching size (1).  When each row is processed very fast and is small, this limits the overall performance.  By setting a higher scanner caching level you can achieve 100x+ the performance with the exact same map-reduce and table.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
