                            <comment id="12723327" author="apurtell" created="Tue, 23 Jun 2009 22:01:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The HBaseConfiguration object is created from the JobConf (TableInputFormat.java, line ~58), so isn&apos;t this sufficient?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
JobConf job = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; JobConf();
&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// ... 
&lt;/span&gt;job.set(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;hbase.client.scanner.caching&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;100&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// ... &lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;No problem to make a convenience method, though...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12723381" author="apurtell" created="Wed, 24 Jun 2009 00:29:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Should the default also be upped to something like 30 as before, or even 100? I mean the default as set by TableMapReduceUtil, not in hbase-default.xml. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12723383" author="jdcryans" created="Wed, 24 Jun 2009 00:36:16 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Should the default also be upped to something like 30 as before, or even 100? I mean the default as set by TableMapReduceUtil, not in hbase-default.xml.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Every time I had to change it that was for a MR job where I was doing heavy processing on each row. So -1 on that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12723396" author="apurtell" created="Wed, 24 Jun 2009 01:52:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ok, then the patch stands as is. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12723420" author="stack" created="Wed, 24 Jun 2009 03:55:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 on patch.  Ryan.... this work for you?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
